    "body": "## Enables `sort_by_key` with `long double` keys on the host\r\n\r\nIn terms of the approach: I disabled radix sort for this key type.  At first I tried to enable it by adding a specialization for `radix_sort_dispatcher` for the case of 16 byte keys.  But then, I also saw that there would be need  to be a specialization for `RadixEncoder` which would require a non-standard `uint128_t`.   Since this is all just for host code, I figured the best route would be to fall back on the less efficient code path.  In addition, I did not add the corresponding logic for the CUDA backend since it wouldn't be usable anyway.\r\n\r\nFixes #7865\r\n\r\n- Sets `use_primitive_sort` to `false` for `long double`\r\n- Implements `TestSortByKeyLongDouble` to enforce that it compiles and runs correctly on the host.\r\n- Also fixes a typo in `_CCCL_ASSERT_IMPL_HOST` caused compilation errors when testing this on a Mac.\r\n\r\n## Checklist\r\n<!-- TODO: - [ ] I am familiar with the [Contributing Guidelines](). -->\r\n- [x] New or existing tests cover these changes.\r\n- [x] The documentation is up to date with these changes.\r\n",
